│ ### Root Cause Analysis ###                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ -------------------- BEGIN --------------------                                                                                                                                  │
│ 1. Understanding the Issue:                                                                                                                                                      │
│ The crash is an assertion failure in LoopVectorizationPlanner::computeBestVF(), specifically the check ensuring the VPlan-based cost model agrees with the legacy cost model,    │
│ unless the VPlan contains additional simplifications. The reproducer loop mixes induction variables of different bitwidths and uses trunc/sext sequences, which often trigger    │
│ differences in cost modeling heuristics. The assertion assumes that disagreements only occur when VPlan has simplifications not accounted for by the legacy model.               │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 2. Analyzing opt's Log:                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The debug-only output doesn't show intermediate logs, but the backtrace pinpoints the first transformation at computeBestVF() where BestFactor and LegacyVF are compared. We     │
│ observed the surrounding code: it precomputes costs, then checks either BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width or planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(...). If neither is true, it │
│ asserts. The planner also filters VFs using willGenerateVectors(P, VF, TTI): it skips VFs that wouldn't produce vector instructions.                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 3. Root Cause Analysis:                                                                                                                                                          │
│ The legacy cost model (selectVectorizationFactor) doesn't apply the willGenerateVectors filter, while the VPlan-based path does. As a result, LegacyVF can select a VF that the  │
│ VPlan path explicitly rejects because it would not actually generate any vector instructions. This is not a “simplification” captured by planContainsAdditionalSimplifications,  │
│ so the assertion fires even though the disagreement is expected and benign. In other words, the two models are being compared under different eligibility criteria: VPlan        │
│ excludes VFs that don’t produce real vector code; the legacy model doesn’t. This can occur in loops like the reproducer where, due to type mismatches and trunc/sext of          │
│ induction, vectorization would degenerate into scalar operations for certain VFs.                                                                                                │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 4. Proposed Edit Point(s):                                                                                                                                                       │
│ - File: llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp, Lines 7364-7369                                                                                                         │
│ Reasoning: Extend the assertion condition to tolerate disagreements when the legacy-selected VF would not generate any vector instructions under the VPlan path. This aligns     │
│ both models' comparison criteria and prevents false positives.                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ Proposed change:                                                                                                                                                                 │
│ Replace:                                                                                                                                                                         │
│   assert((BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width ||                                                                                                                                  │
│           planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width),                                                                                                    │
│                                                 BestFactor.Width, CostCtx,                                                                                                       │
│                                                 OrigLoop, CM)) &&                                                                                                                │
│          " VPlan cost model and legacy cost model disagreed");                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ With:                                                                                                                                                                            │
│   {                                                                                                                                                                              │
│     // If legacy selected a VF that would not generate any vector instructions                                                                                                   │
│     // under the VPlan-based filter, accept the disagreement. The legacy model                                                                                                   │
│     // does not apply willGenerateVectors, while the VPlan-based path does.                                                                                                      │
│     bool LegacyVFGeneratesVectors = true;                                                                                                                                        │
│     if (hasPlanWithVF(LegacyVF.Width)) {                                                                                                                                         │
│       VPlan &LegacyPlan = getPlanFor(LegacyVF.Width);                                                                                                                            │
│       LegacyVFGeneratesVectors = willGenerateVectors(LegacyPlan, LegacyVF.Width, TTI);                                                                                           │
│     }                                                                                                                                                                            │
│     assert((BestFactor.Width == LegacyVF.Width ||                                                                                                                                │
│             !LegacyVFGeneratesVectors ||                                                                                                                                         │
│             planContainsAdditionalSimplifications(getPlanFor(BestFactor.Width),                                                                                                  │
│                                                   BestFactor.Width, CostCtx,                                                                                                     │
│                                                   OrigLoop, CM)) &&                                                                                                              │
│            " VPlan cost model and legacy cost model disagreed");                                                                                                                 │
│   }                                                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ This preserves the original assertion intent but adds a guard for the case where the disagreement is explained by the VPlan's stricter requirement to generate actual vector     │
│ instructions.                                                                                                                                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                  │
│ 5. Conclusion:                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ The crash is due to comparing the VPlan and legacy cost models without accounting for the VPlan-specific willGenerateVectors filter. By allowing the assertion to pass when the  │
│ legacy-chosen VF would not generate any vector instructions under VPlan, we avoid false assertion failures and maintain the integrity of the verification. The fix adjusts the   │
│ assertion to harmonize eligibility criteria between the two paths, preventing the abort for the provided reproducer and similar cases.                                           │
│ --------------------  END  --------------------                                                                                                                                  │
